  <name>ghub4linux</name>
  <summary>Configure Logitech gaming peripherals on Linux</summary>
  <description>
    <p>
      ghub4linux is a Linux alternative to Logitech G Hub for configuring 
      Logitech gaming peripherals. It provides a modern GTK4/libadwaita 
      interface for managing your devices.
    </p>
    <p>Features:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>DPI settings with multiple levels and color indicators</li>
      <li>RGB lighting effects and zone control</li>
      <li>Macro recording and playback with sequences</li>
      <li>Multiple device profiles</li>
      <li>Application-specific profile switching</li>
      <li>Battery status monitoring</li>
      <li>Firmware information and updates</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Supported devices:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>G502 Lightspeed</li>
      <li>G502 X Plus</li>
      <li>PRO DEX 2 (PRO X Superlight 2 DEX)</li>
    </ul>
  </description>
  <launchable type="desktop-id">com.github.mrschnirschuh.ghub4linux.desktop</launchable>
